theorem interior_inter_frontier_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior A ∩ frontier A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- Expand `frontier` and simplify with elementary set identities.
  simp [frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior, Set.inter_diff_self]

theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure A ∩ interior B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨h_clA, h_intB⟩
  rcases h_intB with ⟨U, hU_open, hxU, hU_subB⟩
  -- We will show that `x` belongs to the closure of `A ∩ B`
  -- using the neighbourhood‐based characterisation of `closure`.
  apply (mem_closure_iff).2
  intro V hV_open hxV
  -- Consider the open set `V ∩ U`, which still contains `x`.
  have hW_open : IsOpen (V ∩ U) := hV_open.inter hU_open
  have hxW : x ∈ V ∩ U := And.intro hxV hxU
  -- Because `x ∈ closure A`, this open set meets `A`.
  have h_nonempty : ((V ∩ U) ∩ A).Nonempty := by
    have := (mem_closure_iff).1 h_clA (V ∩ U) hW_open hxW
    -- Rearrange the intersections to a convenient form.
    simpa [Set.inter_assoc, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_comm] using this
  -- Extract a witness `y` of the intersection.
  rcases h_nonempty with ⟨y, ⟨hyV, hyU⟩, hyA⟩
  have hyB : y ∈ B := hU_subB hyU
  -- The point `y` lies in `V ∩ (A ∩ B)`, giving the required non‐emptiness.
  exact ⟨y, And.intro hyV (And.intro hyA hyB)⟩

theorem frontier_eq_diff_interior_of_closed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) :
    frontier A = A \ interior A := by
  have h := frontier_eq_closure_diff_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  simpa [hA.closure_eq] using h
